## Updating to New Releases\par
\par
Create React App is divided into two packages:\par
\par
- `create-react-app` is a global command-line utility that you use to create new projects.\par
- `react-scripts` is a development dependency in the generated projects (including this one).\par
\par
You almost never need to update `create-react-app` itself: it delegates all the setup to `react-scripts`.\par
\par
When you run `create-react-app`, it always creates the project with the latest version of `react-scripts` so you\rquote ll get all the new features and improvements in newly created apps automatically.\par
\par
To update an existing project to a new version of `react-scripts`, [open the changelog](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md), find the version you\rquote re currently on (check `package.json` in this folder if you\rquote re not sure), and apply the migration instructions for the newer versions.\par
\par
In most cases bumping the `react-scripts` version in `package.json` and running `npm install` (or `yarn install`) in this folder should be enough, but it\rquote s good to consult the [changelog](https://github.com/facebook/create-react-app/blob/master/CHANGELOG.md) for potential breaking changes.\par
\par
We commit to keeping the breaking changes minimal so you can upgrade `react-scripts` painlessly.\par
